	Since 2.2.x when I make a ftp to a Linux server from a Win client
the server Hang with no message.
	The server hangs when I ftp my old msdos 6.0 folder, the ftp stops
with the himen.sys archive.
	The problem only appeared with the 3c590-100 Mb card and not with
the 3c309-10 Mb.
	I use RedHat 6.0 and now with kernel 2.2.9.
	The hardware of the server:
	2 PII 450Mhz (now without smp)
	512 Mb Ram 100Mhz
	MotherBoard Iwill BDL 100
	Adaptec Inboard Scsi controler AIC 7890.
	4*9Gb Ultra Scsi2 80Mb/seg.
	Matrox G200.
	1 3c590 Boomerang
	1 3c509
	I have compiled the kernel without smp (with smp dosn't boot, but
this is another history).
